description._content: Description: Ruined castle at Shah Taslim and tomb of an old Saiyid-the Imam Zadeh. Location: Shah Taslim, Persia Description: On the road between Mishun and Godar-i-Cham en route to Gach Qaraguli. Location: Mishun, Godar-i-Cham, Gach Qaraguli, Persia Our Catalogue Reference: Part of CO 1069/714 This image is part of the Colonial Office photographic collection held at The National Archives. Feel free to share it within the spirit of the Commons Please use the comments section below the pictures to share any information you have about the people, places or events shown.
